  "summary": "event-metrics-q3x7 ships postinstall beacon scripts that exfiltrate host info over HTTP",
  "details": "The package's package.json declares a postinstall hook (\"postinstall\": \"node run.js\") that executes on install. The tarball ships beacon19.js and beacon_linux.js, which import child_process, os, and http modules and issue outbound HTTP requests carrying host identifiers obtained via os.hostname() and os.platform(). beacon_linux.js performs an http.request POST referencing the collected hostname, and beacon19.js combines child_process with multiple outbound GET requests. This matches the host-recon-and-beacon pattern: install-time enumeration of host identity followed by network transmission to an external endpoint, with shell-execution capability available via child_process. Installing this package automatically runs the beacon on the installer's machine.",
